text: I find the rune stone in the trailer extremely intriguing and interesting to me. I highly believe the runes are not chosen by random. The top rune is Algiz upside down, which could be understood as the rune of death. Note that death is only one of the many meanings, but it makes sense when we pay attention to the other runes. The middle rune is Reido. It can mean travelling and advancing in physical and/or spiritual way. Besides that, when speaking of shamanism and witchcraft it can stand for ritual. The last rune at the bottom is Perthro. It is a very mysterious and dark rune, and it can mean things like burial, grave, cave or a place under the earth. One can see it also as a rune of the other world. So, all in all, I think that the stone in the trailer could mean something like "doing a death ritual to reach the underworld". As I said before, these runes cannot be chosen randomly. There are deeper meanings in them and this makes me anxiously wait for the movie, as I feel we are dealing with something totally else than the basic horror movies seen nowadays.

text: It is a Re-imagining of the wicker man basically. The things these movies fail to do is what the Wickerman did. A Pagan can watch the Wickerman and see a movie where very misguided Pagans did something bad but it was only possible because of the bigotry pushed on them by the evil Christian who got what he deserved.  These films paint the "christians" as the victims solely. In this case they literally name one of the characters Christian. Mark, Joshua (english version Jesus) , Simon, and Connie (while not directly biblical is the name of several christian figures). Then you have Dani... Daniel without El. The Judge without God. I'm not sure that was intentional but it is there.   Worse these movie generally result in a small uptick in anti Pagan feeling in the general public or encourages bigots to act openly. (Depending on the success of the film and public awareness)   The concept is interesting though.
